comments:
For time stamping mode, in-bound MIDI data is tagged with a time stamp by the DSP. The time stamp is a 3-byte quantity in units of milliseconds. The order of time stamped in-bound MIDI data is:

{monospace:nTime.LowByte, nTime.MidByte, nTime.HighByte, bMidiData}

Refer to command 34h on the characteristics of MIDI UART mode and on how to terminate it.
